{
  "texts": [
    "Its popularity comes mainly from the manipulation of facial appearance (attributes, identity, expression), usually classified into the following categories: (i) entire face synthesis, (ii) attribute manipulation, (iii) identity swap, and (iv) expression swap (i.e., reenactment) (Juefei-Xu et al. 2021).",
    "Deepfake technology itself is neutral, and can be applied for good purposes in many fields including education, entertainment, online social media, healthcare, fashion, and marketing (Westerlund 2019).",
    "It has been used to create digital avatars or virtual assistance to improve the quality of experience in video conferencing (Wang et al. 2021a).",
    "For instance, in Caporusso (2020), the authors utilize deepfake algorithms to extract an accurate model of an individual and generate new content specifically designed for benign purposes.",
    "They create an interactive Digital Twin of a subject, serving as a substitute for in-person or virtual presence."
  ]
}